Functional components are the latest way to write components, but many comapnies in are using class - based components.
Conversion of a functional component to class-based component.

In class based components, check how we access props, why super(props) is called in constructor.
state variables in class- based componenets are created inside the constructor using this.state, this is reserved keyword, state.
to set state variables in class-based components a method setState is used passing an object with updated state variables values

Note: Never update state variables directly (using = or assignement operator), check whether it updates or not, even if it does it will cause in-consistencies in the code.
Behind the scenes state variables are stored as an object, and updating any one of them updates only the particular varibale in the object

Life cycle of react class- based component
life cycle means how a component is mounted on the web page

for a class based component,
when a component using class-based approach is written in code and it gets called:

- the class is instantiated, then
- constructor executes, then
- render function executes, then
- once DOM is loaded for the component then componentDidMount function executes

In case of multiple children, the order of execution for componentDidMount changes
constructor and render methods are called in order of the children
componentDidMount for all children are called at last (kind of together after render methods finishes)

Check - React life cycle diagram - https://projects.wojtekmaj.pl/react-lifecycle-methods-diagram/

React component life cycles have 2 phases
i) Render phase - constructor and render called
ii) React actually updated or shows the DOM then componentDidMount called
that's why for multiple children the Render phase takes place one after the another and constructor and render methods are called in-order
then in Comit phase the DOM is shown in browser, then componentDidMount is called together for all children
